definition.value: This is an AE which is the focused attention on the symptoms of one's distress, and on its possible causes and consequences, as opposed to its solutions, according to the Response Styles Theory proposed by Nolen-Hoeksema (1998).
This is an AE which is a loose connective tissue composed mostly of adipocytes.

This is an AE which is sudden periods of intense fear and discomfort that may include palpitations, sweating, chest pain, shaking, shortness of breath, numbness, or a feeling of impending doom or of losing control.
This is an AE which is the dropping of tears (or welling of tears in the eyes) in response to an emotional state, or pain.
This is an AE which refers a psychological fear of water.
This is an AE which is the unsolicited repetition of vocalizations made by another person (when repeated by the same person, it is called palilalia).
This is an AE which is a state of low mood and aversion to activity.
This is an AE which is a state of tiredness, weariness, fatigue, or lack of energy.

This is an AE which is a loss of the ability to create new memories after the event that caused amnesia, leading to a partial or complete inability to recall the recent past, while long-term memories from before the event remain intact.

This is an AE which is an anxiety disorder in which a person who is otherwise capable of speech becomes unable to speak when exposed to specific situations, specific places, or to specific people, one or multiple of which serving as triggers.

This is an AE which is a sleep disorder causing feelings of panic or dread and typically occurring during the first hours of stage 3 4 non-rapid eye movement (NREM) sleep and lasting for 1 to 10 minutes.
This is an AE which is a non-associative learning process in which repeated administration of a stimulus results in the progressive amplification of a response.
This is an AE which is a common fear or phobia among children and, to a varying degree, adults.

definition.value: This is an AE which is commonly described as a benign neoplasm emerging from the cells that comprise the adrenal cortex.
This is an AE which is the partial or complete wasting away of a part of the adrenal.
This is an AE which is a form of adrenal cortex cell injury which results in the premature death of cells in living tissue by autolysis.
This is an AE which is conditions that interfere with the normal functioning of the adrenal glands.
This is an AE which describes an acute blood loss from a ruptured blood vessel connecting to adrenal glands above kidneys.
This is an AE which is any benign or malignant neoplasms of the adrenal gland, several of which are notable for their tendency to overproduce endocrine hormones.
This is an AE which is disorders of the endocrine system such as adrenal medulla.
This is an AE which is a type of abnormal and excessive growth of adrenal  tissue.

This is an AE which is a condition in which the adrenal glands do not produce adequate amounts of steroid hormones, primarily cortisol; but may also include impaired production of aldosterone (a mineralocorticoid), which regulates sodium conservation, potassium secretion, and water retention.
This is an AE which is a critical care emergency characterized by hemodynamic instability, lethargy, and cardiovascular collapse.

This is an AE which is a rare long-term endocrine disorder characterized by inadequate production of the steroid hormones cortisol and aldosterone by the two outer layers of the cells of the adrenal glands (adrenal cortex), causing adrenal insufficiency.
This is an AE which is a group of autosomal recessive disorders characterized by impaired cortisol synthesis.
This is an AE which indicates insufficient weight gain or absence of appropriate physical growth in children.
This is an AE which is a bacterial infection that results in the death of parts of the body's soft tissue.
This is an AE which is an abnormal amount of lipids (e.g. triglycerides, cholesterol and/or fat phospholipids) in the blood.
This is an AE which is believed to be an autosomal dominant condition in which multiple lipomas are present on the body.
This is an AE which is a benign tumor made of fat tissue.
This is an AE which is a condition that is almost exclusively found in women and results in enlargement of both legs due to deposits of fat under the skin.
This is an AE which is a group of diseases whose hallmark is inflammation of subcutaneous adipose tissue (the fatty layer under the skin  panniculus adiposus).
This is an AE which is a panniculitis on the back of the calves.
This is an AE which is a non-cancerous (benign) skin tumour that originates from cells in the outer layer of the skin.
This is an AE which is a long-term skin disorder.
This is an AE which is  illnesses where trouble occurs in breaking down or synthesizing fats (or fat-like substances).
This is an AE which is the term describing the localized loss of fat tissue.
This is an AE which is the development of symptoms when standing upright that are relieved when reclining.
This is an AE which is a condition in which the mitochondria of a body's cells become damaged or decline significantly in number.
This is an AE which is a lack of something such as mitochondrial enzyme.
This is an AE which is a group of disorders caused by mitochondrial dysfunction.
